'''Jeremy Bulloch''' ([[February 16]], [[1940s#1945|1945]] &ndash; [[December 17]], [[2020]]) was a [[Wikipedia:England|British]] actor best known for playing [[Boba Fett]] in {{Film|V}} and {{Film|VI}}. He was producer [[Robert Watts]]'s half-brother.

His other major roles were in the 1963 film [[Wikipedia:Summer Holiday (1963 film)|''Summer Holiday'']], the [[Wikipedia:BBC|BBC]] television series ''[[wikipedia:Doctor Who|Doctor Who]]'' during the 1970s, and the 1983 [[Wikipedia:List of James Bond films|James Bond film]] [[Wikipedia:Octopussy|''Octopussy'']].<ref name="CNN obituary" /><ref name="BBC obituary">{{WebCite|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-55358301|text=Star Wars' Boba Fett actor Jeremy Bulloch dies aged 75|date=2020-12-18|work=[[Wikipedia:BBC News|BBC News]]|archivedate=20201218140645}}</ref>

==Biography==
[[File:JeremyBullochBobaFett.png|thumb|left|180px|Jeremy Bulloch poses as the bounty hunter Boba Fett.]]
Jeremy Bulloch was born in 1945 in [[Wikipedia:Market Harborough|Market Harborough]] in [[Wikipedia:Leicestershire|Leicestershire]], [[Wikipedia:England|England]].<ref name="CNN obituary" /><ref name="BBC obituary" />

Although Bulloch wore the Boba Fett costume, the voice of the character (prior to being [[List of changes in Star Wars re-releases|replaced]] with [[Temuera Morrison]]'s in the [[Star Wars Trilogy (DVD)|2004 DVD]]) was [[Jason Wingreen]]. According to Bulloch in an interview, he stumbled over Boba Fett's line from {{Film|V}} where he watches a pair of [[stormtrooper]]s load [[Han Solo]] on the ''[[Slave I]]'': although Fett says "Put Captain Solo in the cargo hold" on-screen, Bulloch recalls saying "Put Captain cargo in the Solo hold" during that take.<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-news/7-things-we-learned-from-boba-fett-actors-reddit-ama-100552|text=7 Things We Learned From Boba Fett Actor's Reddit AMA|date=2014-07-10|work=Rolling Stone|archivedate=20191224151058}}</ref>

Bulloch also played [[Lieutenant]] [[Sheckil]] after the original actor was unable to perform. He later had a cameo in {{Film|III}} as [[Captain]] [[Jeremoch Colton]] piloting the ''[[Tantive III]]''.

Bulloch joined [[David Prowse]], [[Michael Sheard]], and [[Orli Shoshan]] in the UK [[fan film]] ''Order of the Sith: Vengeance'' and its sequel, ''Downfall''. Jeremy played the father and commanding officer of the main character, Fuser Marucs. The films were made in support of Save the Children. He made a cameo as himself (a convention attendee) in the Paducah Imperials FanForce feature-length fan film [http://www.starwarsfanboy.com ''Star Wars Fanboy''], ironically muttering the words of Han Solo in ''Return of the Jedi'': "Boba Fett? Where?"

On [[December 17]], [[2020]], Bulloch passed away from Parkinson's disease in hospital at the age of 75, surrounded by his family. Fellow ''Star Wars'' stars [[Mark Hamill]] and [[Daniel Logan]] as well as the Boba Fett Fan Club issued messages of condolences to him. Bulloch left behind a wife, three sons, and ten grandchildren.<ref name="CNN obituary" /><ref name="BBC obituary" />

